# gRPC C++ Channel Creation API

This document covers the public API for creating gRPC client channels and instantiating stubs in C++.

## Overview

A **channel** represents a connection to a gRPC server at a given address. Channels are created via factory functions and are thread-safe. Once created, a channel is passed to a generated stub class to make RPCs.

General pattern:

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/grpcpp.h>
#include "myservice.grpc.pb.h"

// 1. Create a channel
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("localhost:50051",
                                   grpc::InsecureChannelCredentials());

// 2. Create a stub from the channel
auto stub = MyService::NewStub(channel);

// 3. Make RPCs through the stub
grpc::ClientContext ctx;
MyRequest req;
MyResponse resp;
grpc::Status status = stub->MyMethod(&ctx, req, &resp);
```

---

## Channel Factory Functions

Declared in `include/grpcpp/create_channel.h`.

### `grpc::CreateChannel`

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::Channel> grpc::CreateChannel(
    const grpc::string& target,
    const std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials>& creds);
```

Creates a channel with default channel arguments.

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `target` | `const grpc::string&` | URI of the server endpoint, e.g. `"host:port"`. Supports name-resolver prefixes such as `"dns:///host:port"`. |
| `creds` | `std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>` | Credentials for the channel. If null or invalid, a lame channel is returned on which all RPCs fail. |

**Returns:** `std::shared_ptr<grpc::Channel>`

---

### `grpc::CreateCustomChannel`

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::Channel> grpc::CreateCustomChannel(
    const grpc::string& target,
    const std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials>& creds,
    const grpc::ChannelArguments& args);
```

Creates a channel with custom channel arguments. Prefer `CreateChannel` for standard use; use this variant when fine-grained control over channel behavior is required.

> **Warning:** For advanced use and testing only. Override default channel arguments only if necessary.

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `target` | `const grpc::string&` | URI of the server endpoint. |
| `creds` | `std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>` | Credentials for the channel. |
| `args` | `const grpc::ChannelArguments&` | Additional options controlling channel behavior (see [ChannelArguments](#channelarguments)). |

**Returns:** `std::shared_ptr<grpc::Channel>`

---

### `grpc::experimental::CreateCustomChannelWithInterceptors`

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::Channel>
grpc::experimental::CreateCustomChannelWithInterceptors(
    const grpc::string& target,
    const std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials>& creds,
    const grpc::ChannelArguments& args,
    std::vector<std::unique_ptr<
        grpc::experimental::ClientInterceptorFactoryInterface>>
        interceptor_creators);
```

Creates a custom channel with client-side interceptors invoked per call. This API is experimental and subject to change.

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `target` | `const grpc::string&` | URI of the server endpoint. |
| `creds` | `std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>` | Credentials for the channel. |
| `args` | `const grpc::ChannelArguments&` | Channel configuration options. |
| `interceptor_creators` | `std::vector<std::unique_ptr<ClientInterceptorFactoryInterface>>` | Factories for per-call interceptors, applied in order. |

**Returns:** `std::shared_ptr<grpc::Channel>`

---

## Credential Types

Declared in `include/grpcpp/security/credentials.h`.

### Base Classes

#### `grpc::ChannelCredentials`

Abstract base class encapsulating all state needed to authenticate a client with a server at the channel level. All credential factory functions return a `std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>`.

#### `grpc::CallCredentials`

Abstract base class for per-call credentials. These are combined with channel credentials via `CompositeChannelCredentials` or used standalone.

---

### Insecure Credentials

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials> grpc::InsecureChannelCredentials();
```

Creates credentials for an **unencrypted, unauthenticated** channel. No TLS, no identity verification.

**Use only for:** local development, testing, or trusted private networks.

```cpp
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("localhost:50051",
                                   grpc::InsecureChannelCredentials());
```

---

### SSL/TLS Credentials

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials> grpc::SslCredentials(
    const grpc::SslCredentialsOptions& options);
```

Creates credentials for a TLS-encrypted channel.

#### `grpc::SslCredentialsOptions`

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `pem_root_certs` | `grpc::string` | PEM-encoded server root CA certificates. If empty, the system default roots are used (can be overridden via `GRPC_DEFAULT_SSL_ROOTS_FILE_PATH`). |
| `pem_private_key` | `grpc::string` | PEM-encoded client private key. Empty for server-only auth (no mutual TLS). |
| `pem_cert_chain` | `grpc::string` | PEM-encoded client certificate chain. Empty for server-only auth. |

**Server-only authentication (one-way TLS):**

```cpp
grpc::SslCredentialsOptions opts;
// Use system default roots; no client certificate
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("example.com:443",
                                   grpc::SslCredentials(opts));
```

**Mutual TLS (mTLS):**

```cpp
grpc::SslCredentialsOptions opts;
opts.pem_root_certs  = ReadFile("ca.pem");
opts.pem_private_key = ReadFile("client.key");
opts.pem_cert_chain  = ReadFile("client.crt");

auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("example.com:443",
                                   grpc::SslCredentials(opts));
```

---

### Composite Channel Credentials

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials> grpc::CompositeChannelCredentials(
    const std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials>& channel_creds,
    const std::shared_ptr<grpc::CallCredentials>& call_creds);
```

Combines channel-level credentials with per-call credentials. Every call on the resulting channel automatically attaches the call credentials.

| Parameter | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `channel_creds` | The underlying channel credentials (e.g. SSL). |
| `call_creds` | Per-call credentials to attach (e.g. an access token). |

```cpp
// Combine SSL transport security with an OAuth2 access token
auto call_creds  = grpc::AccessTokenCredentials(my_oauth2_token);
auto chan_creds  = grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions());
auto composite   = grpc::CompositeChannelCredentials(chan_creds, call_creds);

auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("api.example.com:443", composite);
```

---

### Google Default Credentials

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials> grpc::GoogleDefaultCredentials();
```

Builds credentials using Application Default Credentials (ADC) — suitable for services running on Google Cloud (GCE, GKE, Cloud Run, etc.) or authenticated via `gcloud auth application-default login`.

> **Warning:** Only use when connecting to a Google endpoint.

```cpp
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("pubsub.googleapis.com:443",
                                   grpc::GoogleDefaultCredentials());
```

---

### ALTS Credentials (experimental)

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials> grpc::experimental::AltsCredentials(
    const grpc::experimental::AltsCredentialsOptions& options);
```

Application Layer Transport Security — Google's mutual-authentication protocol for same-machine or same-datacenter connections.

#### `grpc::experimental::AltsCredentialsOptions`

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `target_service_accounts` | `std::vector<grpc::string>` | Acceptable service accounts of the target endpoint. Authentication fails if the server's account does not match. Leave empty to accept any account. |

```cpp
grpc::experimental::AltsCredentialsOptions opts;
opts.target_service_accounts = {"serviceaccount@myproject.iam.gserviceaccount.com"};

auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("backend:8080",
    grpc::experimental::AltsCredentials(opts));
```

---

### Local Credentials (experimental)

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<grpc::ChannelCredentials> grpc::experimental::LocalCredentials(
    grpc_local_connect_type type);
```

Credentials for local connections (UDS or loopback). `type` is one of:

| Value | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `LOCAL_TCP` | Local TCP (loopback) connection. |
| `UDS` | Unix Domain Socket connection. |

```cpp
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("unix:///tmp/my.sock",
    grpc::experimental::LocalCredentials(UDS));
```

---

### Additional Call Credentials

These are attached to a channel via `CompositeChannelCredentials` or applied per-call.

| Factory | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `grpc::AccessTokenCredentials(token)` | OAuth2 bearer token obtained out-of-band. |
| `grpc::GoogleComputeEngineCredentials()` | GCE service account credentials. |
| `grpc::ServiceAccountJWTAccessCredentials(json_key, lifetime_secs)` | Service account JWT; lifetime capped at 3600 s. |
| `grpc::GoogleRefreshTokenCredentials(json_refresh_token)` | OAuth2 refresh token. |
| `grpc::GoogleIAMCredentials(auth_token, authority_selector)` | Google IAM authorization. |
| `grpc::MetadataCredentialsFromPlugin(plugin)` | User-defined metadata credentials via `MetadataCredentialsPlugin`. |
| `grpc::ExternalAccountCredentials(json_string, scopes)` | Workload/workforce identity federation credentials. |
| `grpc::experimental::StsCredentials(options)` | STS OAuth Token Exchange (IETF draft). |

---

## ChannelArguments

Declared in `include/grpcpp/support/channel_arguments.h`.

`grpc::ChannelArguments` is a configuration object passed to `CreateCustomChannel`. It exposes typed setters for common gRPC knobs as well as generic key/value setters for lower-level options.

### Construction

```cpp
grpc::ChannelArguments args;  // default constructor, no arguments set
```

### Typed Setters

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `SetSslTargetNameOverride(name)` | Override the server name used for SSL/TLS host-name verification. Use with caution in production. |
| `SetCompressionAlgorithm(algorithm)` | Set the default compression algorithm for the channel (`GRPC_COMPRESS_GZIP`, etc.). |
| `SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(size)` | Maximum inbound message size in bytes (`-1` = unlimited). |
| `SetMaxSendMessageSize(size)` | Maximum outbound message size in bytes (`-1` = unlimited). |
| `SetUserAgentPrefix(prefix)` | Prepend a string to the gRPC user-agent header. |
| `SetLoadBalancingPolicyName(name)` | Set the LB policy (e.g. `"round_robin"`, `"grpclb"`). |
| `SetGrpclbFallbackTimeout(ms)` | Milliseconds to wait for a non-empty server list from a balancer before falling back to resolver addresses. |
| `SetResourceQuota(quota)` | Attach a `grpc::ResourceQuota` to limit memory used by the channel. |
| `SetServiceConfigJSON(json)` | Supply a service config in JSON form (primarily for unit tests). |
| `SetSocketMutator(mutator)` | Apply a low-level socket mutator. |

### Generic Setters

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `SetInt(key, value)` | Set an integer channel argument by raw key string. |
| `SetString(key, value)` | Set a string channel argument by raw key string. |
| `SetPointer(key, ptr)` | Set a pointer channel argument (no ownership transfer). |
| `SetPointerWithVtable(key, ptr, vtable)` | Set a pointer with a vtable that handles copy/destroy/compare. |

### Example

```cpp
grpc::ChannelArguments args;
args.SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(16 * 1024 * 1024);  // 16 MiB
args.SetMaxSendMessageSize(16 * 1024 * 1024);
args.SetUserAgentPrefix("my-client/1.0");
args.SetLoadBalancingPolicyName("round_robin");

auto channel = grpc::CreateCustomChannel(
    "backend.example.com:443",
    grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions()),
    args);
```

---

## Complete Examples

### Example 1: Insecure channel (local development)

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/grpcpp.h>
#include "helloworld.grpc.pb.h"

int main() {
    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("localhost:50051",
                                       grpc::InsecureChannelCredentials());
    auto stub = helloworld::Greeter::NewStub(channel);

    grpc::ClientContext ctx;
    helloworld::HelloRequest req;
    helloworld::HelloReply reply;
    req.set_name("World");

    grpc::Status status = stub->SayHello(&ctx, req, &reply);
    if (status.ok()) {
        std::cout << reply.message() << std::endl;
    }
    return 0;
}
```

### Example 2: TLS channel with system roots

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/grpcpp.h>

auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel(
    "api.example.com:443",
    grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions()));
// SslCredentialsOptions default-constructed → uses system CA roots
```

### Example 3: Mutual TLS (mTLS)

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/grpcpp.h>
#include <fstream>
#include <sstream>

std::string ReadFile(const std::string& path) {
    std::ifstream f(path);
    std::ostringstream ss;
    ss << f.rdbuf();
    return ss.str();
}

int main() {
    grpc::SslCredentialsOptions opts;
    opts.pem_root_certs  = ReadFile("/etc/certs/ca.pem");
    opts.pem_private_key = ReadFile("/etc/certs/client.key");
    opts.pem_cert_chain  = ReadFile("/etc/certs/client.crt");

    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("secure.example.com:443",
                                       grpc::SslCredentials(opts));
    return 0;
}
```

### Example 4: SSL + OAuth2 access token (CompositeChannelCredentials)

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/grpcpp.h>

std::string FetchOAuth2Token();  // your token-fetching logic

int main() {
    auto ssl   = grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions());
    auto token = grpc::AccessTokenCredentials(FetchOAuth2Token());
    auto creds = grpc::CompositeChannelCredentials(ssl, token);

    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("api.example.com:443", creds);
    return 0;
}
```

### Example 5: Custom channel arguments

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/grpcpp.h>

int main() {
    grpc::ChannelArguments args;
    args.SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(64 * 1024 * 1024);  // 64 MiB
    args.SetMaxSendMessageSize(64 * 1024 * 1024);
    args.SetLoadBalancingPolicyName("round_robin");
    args.SetUserAgentPrefix("my-service/2.3.1");

    auto channel = grpc::CreateCustomChannel(
        "lb.example.com:443",
        grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions()),
        args);
    return 0;
}
```

---

## Header Summary

| Header | Contents |
|--------|----------|
| `include/grpcpp/create_channel.h` | `CreateChannel`, `CreateCustomChannel`, `CreateCustomChannelWithInterceptors` |
| `include/grpcpp/security/credentials.h` | `ChannelCredentials`, `CallCredentials`, all credential factory functions, `SslCredentialsOptions`, `MetadataCredentialsPlugin` |
| `include/grpcpp/support/channel_arguments.h` | `ChannelArguments` |
| `include/grpcpp/channel.h` | `grpc::Channel` (the channel object itself) |

